        "title": "이다,아니다",
        "content": [
            {
                "title": "The verb 이다 means to be. The verb 아니다 means not to be.",
                "details": "This is our first lesson with grammar. For Korean grammar, please remember that the structure is Subject-Object-Verb. So the Verb goes <em>last</em> in the sentence, and is usually the most important part of the sentence, as the verb endings can change as you will find out.<br/><br/>For 이다, when the noun ends in a consonant, the ending 이에요 is used. When the noun ends in a vowel, 예요 is used. The casual ending form is 이야. <br/> For 아니다, the endings 아니에요 (polite) and 아니야 (plain) are used. <br/>Now you can say Noun A is/is not Noun B!<br/> Note that you can click on any of the Korean words below to get the translation and/or add it to the vocab list."
            }
        ],
